H0.text: What African nation is known in parts of Asia by the local names of two of its famous cities Marrakech and Fes. Egypt

H1.text: What African nation is known in parts of Asia by the local names of two of its famous cities Marrakech and Fes. Morocco's neighbor, Algeria

H2.text: What African nation is known in parts of Asia by the local names of two of its famous cities Marrakech and Fes. South Africa

H3.text: What African nation is known in parts of Asia by the local names of two of its famous cities Marrakech and Fes. Maroc

A4.text: In Turkish, Morocco is known as Fas, a name derived from its medieval capital of Fes (فاس).

A5.text: In other parts of the Islamic world, for example in Egyptian and Middle Eastern Arabic literature before the mid-20th century, Morocco was commonly referred to as Murrakush (مراكش).
